---
description: debugging workflow for errors, failing tests, regressions, strange behavior, and why-is-this-broken tasks. use when you need root-cause analysis and proof instead of guesswork.
alwaysApply: false
---

- Capture the symptom and expected behavior first.
- Reproduce or narrow the failing path before patching when possible.
- Form a short root-cause hypothesis before editing.
- Prefer fixes that remove the cause, not band-aids that only hide symptoms.
- After changes, rerun the closest proof:
  - the same failing test or command
  - a targeted smoke path
  - build or typecheck if interfaces changed
- In the handoff, explicitly separate:
  - reproduced or not reproduced
  - verified, partially verified, or unverified
  - root cause or likely cause if still inferential
- If a full repro is impossible, say what evidence you do have and the next best check.
